\begin_layout Itemize
The mean is a 
\series bold
population
\series default
 quantity.
 It is a 
\series bold
fixed
\series default
 number.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
The average is a 
\series bold
sample
\series default
 quantity.
 It is a 
\series bold
random variable
\series default
.
 
\begin_inset VSpace 0.5cm*
\end_inset

 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
In statistics, we 
\series bold
estimate
\series default
: use the sample average to make a guess (
\series bold
estimate
\series default
) about the mean 
\end_layout

