\begin_layout Itemize
Prior to 
\series bold
election
\series default
 day, we are interested in predicting what percentage of votes each candidate
 gets 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
The 
\series bold
population
\series default
 is: all voters 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
54%
\series default
 of voters is going to choose candidate A 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
But we 
\series bold
do not know
\series default
 this number: it is the 
\series bold
population
\series default
 parameter 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
It is not cost-effective (nor feasible) to ask 
\series bold
all
\series default
 the people 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
We can obtain a 
\series bold
sample
\series default
 of 100 individuals, and ask them 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
In that sample, we find that 
\series bold
59%
\series default
 of individuals would vote for candidate A 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
end{frame}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
begin{frame}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 
\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout

{
\end_layout

\end_inset

Example: voting (2)
\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout

}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Note 1: 59% 
\begin_inset Formula $\neq$
\end_inset

 54% 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Note 2: Had I asked a different group of people, I would have had a 
\series bold
different
\series default
 number 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Note 3: 59% is our 
\series bold
best guess
\series default
.
 It may be better to report a 
\series bold
confidence interval
\series default
 rather than our best guess.
 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

With 95% confidence, the percentage of people that would vote for candidate
 A is in 
\series bold
between
\series default
 53% and 65%.
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Note 4: The reason that this is important, is that the uncertainty could
 have been much 
\series bold
higher
\series default
.
 The research might have only been able to conclude that the 95%-CI is 
\series bold
(10%,90%)
\series default
 
\end_layout

